stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 1: COMMUNICATION FOUNDATIONS) Tj ET
54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (Why Communication is the Foundation of Love) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (Research by Dr. John Gottman, who studied thousands of couples over four decades, shows) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (that the number one predictor of relationship success or failure is the quality of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (communication between partners. It is not compatibility, shared interests, or even love) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (alone that keeps couples together. It is the ability to communicate needs, resolve) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.4 Td (conflicts, and maintain emotional connection through conversation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (The good news is that communication is a skill, not a talent. No one is born a great) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (communicator. These skills can be learned, practiced, and improved at any stage of a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 522.6 Td (relationship, whether you have been together 6 months or 30 years.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 492.8 Td (The Four Horsemen of Relationship Destruction) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 465.0 Td (Dr. Gottman identified four communication patterns that predict divorce with over 90%) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 451.0 Td (accuracy. Recognizing these in yourself is the first step to changing them:) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 423.2 Td (1. Criticism \(Attacking your partner's character\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 407.2 Td (Criticism is different from a complaint. A complaint addresses a specific behavior.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 393.2 Td (Criticism attacks who your partner IS as a person.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 379.2 Td (Criticism example: You never help around the house. You are so lazy and selfish.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 365.2 Td (Healthy alternative: I felt overwhelmed with housework this week. Could we talk about) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 351.2 Td (dividing chores more evenly?) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 323.4 Td (2. Contempt \(Superiority, disgust, disrespect\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 307.4 Td (Contempt is the single greatest predictor of divorce. It includes eye-rolling, sarcasm,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 293.4 Td (name-calling, mocking, and hostile humor. It communicates: I am better than you.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 279.4 Td (Contempt example: Oh, you forgot to pay the bill AGAIN? I should not be surprised.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 265.4 Td (Healthy alternative: I noticed the bill was missed. Can we set up autopay so we do not) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 251.4 Td (have to worry about it?) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 223.6 Td (3. Defensiveness \(Refusing responsibility\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 207.6 Td (Defensiveness is a way of blaming your partner. It says: The problem is not me, it is you.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 193.6 Td (It prevents resolution because no one takes ownership.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 179.6 Td (Defensive example: It is not MY fault we were late. YOU took forever getting ready.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 165.6 Td (Healthy alternative: You are right, I should have started getting ready earlier. I will) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 151.6 Td (set an alarm next time.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 123.8 Td (4. Stonewalling \(Shutting down, withdrawing\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 107.8 Td (Stonewalling happens when one partner completely withdraws from interaction. They may) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 93.8 Td (physically leave, go silent, or appear to be listening but are actually checked out.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
