BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 2: ACTIVE LISTENING SKILLS) Tj ET
54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (The Art of Truly Hearing Your Partner) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (Most people listen to respond rather than listening to understand. Active listening is a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (deliberate practice where you give your full attention to your partner, seek to understand) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (their perspective completely, and communicate that understanding back to them before) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (sharing your own thoughts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 564.6 Td (When your partner feels truly heard, they feel safe, valued, and connected. Most arguments) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (escalate not because of the issue itself, but because one or both partners do not feel) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (heard.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 506.8 Td (The HEAR Method) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 479.0 Td (- H - Halt: Stop what you are doing. Put down your phone. Turn toward your partner.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 465.0 Td (- E - Empathize: Try to understand their feelings, not just their words.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 451.0 Td (- A - Acknowledge: Reflect back what you heard to confirm understanding.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 437.0 Td (- R - Respond: Only after they confirm you understood, share your perspective.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 407.2 Td (Active Listening Practice Scenarios) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 379.4 Td (Take turns being the speaker and the listener for each scenario. The speaker shares for 3) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 365.4 Td (minutes uninterrupted. The listener practices the HEAR method.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 337.6 Td (Scenario 1) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 321.6 Td (Speaker: Share about something stressful at work this week. Listener: Practice reflecting) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 307.6 Td (back what you hear without offering solutions.) Tj ET
