BT /F2 12 Tf 54 582.4 Td (The Time-Out Protocol) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 554.6 Td (When emotions flood during an argument \(heart rate above 100 BPM\), productive) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 540.6 Td (communication becomes physiologically impossible. The time-out protocol prevents damage:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 516.8 Td (- Step 1: Either partner can call a time-out \(use agreed signal or word\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 502.8 Td (- Step 2: Separate for a minimum of 20 minutes \(this is physiological, not optional\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 488.8 Td (- Step 3: During the break, do something calming \(walk, breathe, listen to music\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 474.8 Td (- Step 4: Do NOT rehearse arguments or build your case during the break) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 460.8 Td (- Step 5: Return at the agreed time and resume with softened startups) Tj ET
