BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 6: WEEKLY & MONTHLY RITUALS) Tj ET
54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (The Power of Relationship Rituals) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (Happy couples do not leave their connection to chance. They build regular rituals into) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (their lives that ensure they stay emotionally connected regardless of how busy, stressful,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (or routine life becomes. These are not grand gestures but consistent, small practices that) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (compound into deep intimacy over time.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 558.6 Td (Daily Connection Rituals \(5-10 minutes\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 526.8 Td (1. The 6-Second Kiss) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.8 Td (Research shows that a kiss lasting at least 6 seconds is long enough to create a moment of) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 496.8 Td (genuine connection and release bonding hormones. Make this your hello and goodbye ritual.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 469.0 Td (2. Highs, Lows, and Gratitudes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 453.0 Td (Each evening, share: one high point of your day, one low point, and one thing you are) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 439.0 Td (grateful for about your partner. This takes 5 minutes and maintains emotional awareness.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 411.2 Td (3. The Stress-Reducing Conversation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 395.2 Td (Spend 10-15 minutes at the end of each day talking about stresses OUTSIDE the relationship) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 381.2 Td (\(work, friends, family\). The listener's job is only to be supportive, not to give advice.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 353.4 Td (4. Goodnight Ritual) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 337.4 Td (Go to bed at the same time at least a few nights per week. This is when many couples have) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 323.4 Td (their best conversations and feel most connected.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 293.6 Td (Weekly Rituals) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 261.8 Td (The Weekly Check-In \(30 minutes\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 245.8 Td (Schedule 30 minutes each week \(same time\) to discuss your relationship directly. This) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 231.8 Td (prevents issues from building up and ensures you stay proactive about connection.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 208.0 Td (Our weekly check-in time: _______ Day: _______) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 180.2 Td (Weekly Check-In Agenda:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 164.2 Td (- 1. Appreciations: Each share 3 things you appreciated about your partner this week) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 150.2 Td (- 2. Logistics: Calendar review, upcoming events, coordination) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 136.2 Td (- 3. Issues: Any small things that need addressing? \(use softened startups\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 122.2 Td (- 4. Fun: Plan something enjoyable for the coming week) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 108.2 Td (- 5. Intimacy: Check in on physical and emotional connection) Tj ET
endstream
