BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (CHAPTER 8: REBUILDING TRUST) Tj ET
54 684.0 m 558 684.0 l 0.5 w S
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 658.2 Td (When Trust Has Been Broken) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 630.4 Td (Trust is the foundation of every healthy relationship. When it is broken, whether through) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 616.4 Td (dishonesty, betrayal, broken promises, or emotional unavailability, the relationship) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 602.4 Td (enters a critical period. Rebuilding trust is possible but requires consistent effort,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (patience, accountability, and genuine willingness to change from both partners.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 564.6 Td (This chapter provides a framework for the difficult work of trust repair. If the breach) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 550.6 Td (was severe \(infidelity, addiction, abuse\), please work with a licensed couples therapist) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.6 Td (alongside this workbook.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 506.8 Td (Understanding Trust) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 479.0 Td (Trust is not a single thing. It is built from multiple components:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 455.2 Td (- RELIABILITY: You do what you say you will do, consistently) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 441.2 Td (- HONESTY: You tell the truth, even when it is uncomfortable) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 427.2 Td (- VULNERABILITY: You share your inner world authentically) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 413.2 Td (- SAFETY: Your partner feels physically and emotionally safe with you) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 399.2 Td (- LOYALTY: You protect the relationship from outside threats) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 385.2 Td (- ACCOUNTABILITY: You take responsibility when you make mistakes) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 355.4 Td (Trust Assessment) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 327.6 Td (Rate each area of trust from 1 \(completely broken\) to 10 \(fully intact\):) Tj ET
